    if i % 3 == 0 and i % 5 == 0:
        print("FizzBuzz")
    elif i % 3 == 0:
        print("Fizz")
    elif i % 5 == 0:
        print("Buzz")
    else:
        print(i)
```

This code prints numbers from 1 to 100, but for multiples of 3 it prints "Fizz" instead of the number, for multiples of 5 it prints "Buzz", and for multiples of both 3 and 5 it prints "FizzBuzz".

